\section{Thesis outline}
This thesis is organized as follows. \autoref{chapter:overview} gives an overview of the market of spectrum auctions and explain the necessity of such auctions, with detail on the German spectrum auction in 2015. The following \autoref{chapter:theory} will introduce important concepts and terminology of auction theory. Subsequently, \autoref{chapter:experiment} explains the data acquisition and analysis that gained insights for production of the value model. \autoref{chapter:simulation} is the heart of this thesis, explaining the simulation process and the results. Lastly, \autoref{chapter:conclusion} draws final conclusions from the simulation data and gives an outlook for future work.